<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 03 at 3:14PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Snow covered roads and variable visibility for the evening
commute...
Light snow, reducing visibility to a half mile or less at times,
will continue late this afternoon into the early evening hours.
Although most locations will only receive an inch or less of
snow accumulation, temperatures in the lower 20s and northeast
winds gusting to around 30 mph will lead to snow covered roads and
slower traffic. Motorists are urged to use caution and account
for the variable driving conditions by allowing extra time.</description>
